<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="65" pageId="8" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,2013]" lastBlockId="9.[247,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="65" pageId="8" pageNumber="64">
Remark: 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick, E." box="[354,524,1986,2012]" pageId="8" pageNumber="64" refId="ref10896" refString="Meyrick, E. (1916 - 1923 b) Exotic Microlepidoptera. Vol. II. E. W. Classey, Hampton, Middlesex, 640 pp." type="book" year="1916">Meyrick (1916</bibRefCitation>
– 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick, E." box="[539,595,1986,2012]" pageId="8" pageNumber="64" refId="ref10926" refString="Meyrick, E. (1923 - 1930 c) Exotic Microlepidoptera. Vol. III. E. W. Classey, Hampton, Middlesex, 640 pp." type="book" year="1923">1923</bibRefCitation>
b) recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1918" box="[736,882,1986,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Homaloxestis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xylotripta">
<emphasis box="[736,882,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="64">H. xylotripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Peshawar which was in North-West 
<collectingCountry box="[1379,1437,1986,2012]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="64">India</collectingCountry>
previously but after 1947, Peshawar become the part of 
<collectingCountry box="[875,974,151,177]" name="Pakistan" pageId="9" pageNumber="65">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
. So the Indian distribution of this species is doubtful. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, S. R. &amp; Wang, S. X." box="[494,715,187,213]" pageId="9" pageNumber="65" pagination="79 - 88" refId="ref10323" refString="Liu, S. R. &amp; Wang, S. X. (2014) The genus Homaloxestis Meyrick (Lepidoptera: Lecithoceridae) from China, with descriptions of two new species. Zootaxa, 3760 (1), 79 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3760.1.5" type="journal article" year="2014">Liu &amp; Wang (2014)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1019,1089,187,213]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="65">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1100,1158,187,213]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="65">India</collectingCountry>
(without mentioning the exact locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[431,493,223,249]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="65">India</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[512,582,223,249]" name="Nepal" pageId="9" pageNumber="65">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[592,690,223,249]" name="Pakistan" pageId="9" pageNumber="65">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[700,800,223,249]" name="Thailand" pageId="9" pageNumber="65">Thailand</collectingCountry>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Park, K. T." box="[853,985,223,249]" pageId="9" pageNumber="65" pagination="33 - 43" refId="ref11114" refString="Park, K. T. (2004) Genus Homaloxestis Meyrick of Thailand, with Description of Five New Species (Lepidoptera, Lecithoceridae). Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 7 (1), 33 - 43. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 1226 - 8615 (08) 60199 - 5" type="journal article" year="2004">Park (2004)</bibRefCitation>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1157,1260,223,249]" name="Thailand" pageId="9" pageNumber="65">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. Further studies on this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[446,504,259,285]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="65">India</collectingCountry>
may apprise the exact distributional record of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1191,1252,259,285]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="65">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
